= Belief in _al-Ṭiyarah_ (bad omens/superstitions)

*Definition:*

Linguistically: Derived from the word _*tatayyur*_, meaning optimism or
pessimism based on something.

In Islām: Pessimism caused by something seen, heard, or known.

*Ruling on Bad Omens:*

Bad omens contradicts Tawḥīd (Islamic monotheism) in two ways:

1. The superstitious person cuts off their trust in Allāh and relies on
  something else.
2. They become attached to something unreal, based on illusion or imagination.

Evidence for its prohibition:

Allāh says,

#quran-block[
  فَإِذَا جَآءَتۡهُمُ ٱلۡحَسَنَةُ قَالُواْ لَنَا هَٰذِهِۦۖ وَإِن تُصِبۡهُمۡ
  سَيِّئَةٞ يَطَّيَّرُواْ بِمُوسَىٰ وَمَن مَّعَهُۥٓۗ أَلَآ إِنَّمَا
  طَٰٓئِرُهُمۡ عِندَ ٱللَّهِ وَلَٰكِنَّ أَكۡثَرَهُمۡ لَا يَعۡلَمُونَ ١٣١
][
  But whenever good came to them, they said: "Ours is this." And if evil afflicted
  them, they ascribed it to evil omens connected with Musa (Moses) and those with
  him. Be informed! Verily, their evil omens are with Allāh but most of them know
  not. (Al-Aʿrāf Q7:131)
]

The Prophet Muḥammad #pbuh said,

#hadith-block[
  لَا عَدْوَى، وَلَا صَفَرَ، وَلَا هَامَةَ». فَقَالَ أَعْرَابِيٌّ: يَا رَسُولَ
  اللَّهِ، فَمَا بَالُ الْإِبِلِ تَكُونُ فِي الرَّمْلِ كَأَنَّهَا الظِّبَاءُ،
  فَيَأْتِي الْبَعِيرُ الْأَجْرَبُ فَيَدْخُلُ فِيهَا فَيُجْرِبُهَا كُلَّهَا؟
  فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ: «فَمَنْ أَعْدَى الْأَوَّلَ؟»
][
  “There is no infection (that spreads independently), no Safar, and no Hama.” A
  Bedouin said: “O Messenger of Allāh, how is it that camels in the desert are as
  healthy as deer, then a mangy camel mixes with them and they all get the
  disease?” The Messenger of Allāh replied: “Then who caused the first one to be
  infected?”@muslim[vol. 6, pp. 43--44, \#2285]
]

He #pbuh also said,

#hadith-block[
  الطِّيَرَةُ شِرْكٌ، الطِّيَرَةُ شِرْكٌ
